{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Increase the threshold at which child benefit is repaid from \u00a350k to \u00a360k",
        "additional_details": "When the high income child benefit charge was introduced in 2013 the higher rate tax threshold was \u00a342,475. This was \u00a37,525 lower than the \u00a350k threshold.\r\n\r\nNow the higher rate tax threshold is \u00a350,270 - above the \u00a350k threshold at which child benefit must be repaid. This has not increased in line with the tax thresholds or with inflation, which is currently at the highest rate in decades.\r\n\r\nIt is only fair that the child benefit thresholds are increased in line with the tax bands and inflation.",
        "background": "Child benefit must be repaid when an individual earns over \u00a350k. The amount to be repaid increases on a sliding scale of 1% for every \u00a3100 up to earnings of \u00a360k at which the full amount is repaid. \r\n\r\nI propose that the lower threshold is increased to \u00a360k and the upper threshold to \u00a375k.",
